				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Camp Stealing<a name="52261"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 16 04 11:07 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hi everyone, my first post <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" />  I am putting it in here because I didnt want my first post to be a rant... lol
<br />

<br />
Anyway, I was wondering if any action can be taken against people who steal mobs that you are camping/kiting. The reason I ask is because today, I was camping the Goblin Warrior camp in BB. Whilst I was in the middle of kiting 3 gobs a level 14 warrior pops over and decides to help himself to my mobs. At first I assumed he thought I was in trouble and was trying to help me out, but my /tells of please leave my mobs alone went unanswered.  So I wait for the camp to re-pop... As soon as it does to warrior appears again, pulls all the gobs, loots and runs.  This happens 2 more times, with no replies to any of my tells asking him to leave my area alone.
<br />

<br />
I do finally get him to talk and he tells me that is is clearing all the gob camps and farming plat, and that I should get out of his way.  He also tells me I should go somewhere else and get a few more levels before I camp the area ( I laughed at that, I would like to so him solo 2 yellows and 1 white at lvl7!)
<br />

<br />
He did finally zone and leave me the camp.  I got his name and the guild he belongs to... Should I take this up with his guild, or just suck it in and move on?
<br />

<br />
Cheers
<br />
Tolil</span></td>
