				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Camp Stealing<a name="52309"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 16 04 3:04 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>KS'ing is prohibited under the &quot;Play Nice&quot; rules, but there is very little SoE can do about it as the offending action would have to be witnessed as it happens by the SoE rep.  You could try /petitioning it immediately, particularly if you have some evidence in /chat that would implicate the offending party (and you might have had some in your case).
<br />

<br />
Camp stealing is even harder to address as SoE expects you and the other players to work out a solution to sharing the camp (and you should share the camp somehow, if only for etiquitte's sake).  People have differing views on camps, and I tend to not even confront someone I see already camping a spot as there are many more zones and travel in general is much easier in the game than it was since EQ first started.</span></td>
