				<td colspan="2"><span>Personally my first point of call if diplomacy has failed is to speak with an Officer frokm the other person's guild. Most of the time the embarassment alone will be enough to defuse the situation.
<br />

<br />
If the guild does not care or the other person id guildless there is very little recourse to you other than to /petition or move elsewhere. It is a sad fact in EQ that most of the time anti-social behaviour does win out. The only encouragement I can offer here is that it's fairly rare to encounter it at such low levels these days. Most of the time the anti-social activities occur at the high levels, particularly amongst players that have gotten used to 'cutthroat' raiding rules in guilds that prefer to race (or just steamroll) than share.
<br />

